WEBVTT

00:02.760 --> 00:04.592
Oh, great.
We got the Prius...

00:04.680 --> 00:07.195
that could make dinner reservations,
buy movie tickets, tell us the weather.

00:07.280 --> 00:10.000
I just want one that opens.
[ Beeping ]

00:10.080 --> 00:11.480
[ Mitchell ] Maybe we should
have gotten that one.

00:11.600 --> 00:12.590
[ Beeps ] [ Cameron Chuckles ]

00:12.680 --> 00:14.034
Mitchell?

00:14.200 --> 00:15.919
Oh-Oh, my God, Teddy. Cam, this is Teddy.
[ Chuckles ]

00:16.000 --> 00:17.878
Teddy? Teddy Teddy?

00:17.960 --> 00:19.838
Doc-Dr. Teddy!

00:19.920 --> 00:24.039
Teddy was Mitch's one significant
boyfriend before me.

00:24.120 --> 00:26.271
Uh, Mitch had recently
just come out.

00:26.360 --> 00:29.353
And as he put it, it was
hard to love someone else...

00:29.440 --> 00:31.875
if he couldn't love himself.

00:31.960 --> 00:34.156
I actually said those words?

00:34.240 --> 00:35.959
It's kind of hard
to love myself right now.

00:36.040 --> 00:38.111
You were the one who said,
"I need some time.

00:38.200 --> 00:39.714
I'll call you
when I heal more."

00:39.800 --> 00:41.234
- Ten years later-
- Aww!

00:41.360 --> 00:44.034
I never said that.
Time to heal more.

00:44.120 --> 00:45.600
That's so sweet and sensitive.

00:45.680 --> 00:47.200
Why did you kill that part
of yourself?

00:47.280 --> 00:48.634
You know, I'm hosting
a fund-raiser...

00:48.720 --> 00:49.870
for the hospital this weekend...

00:49.960 --> 00:51.474
at that roller rink on South Main.

00:51.560 --> 00:52.835
Any chance you guys can come?

00:52.960 --> 00:54.474
Yeah. Absolutely. We'll be there.
Possibly.

00:54.560 --> 00:57.075
- Okay.
- Great. So 4:00, Saturday.

00:57.200 --> 00:58.680
I'm so glad
I bumped into you all.

00:58.760 --> 01:00.831
Us too. Say bye, Lily!

01:00.920 --> 01:03.151
- Bye, Lily.
- [ All Laugh ]

01:03.240 --> 01:04.468
I taught her that, so-

01:04.599 --> 01:06.557
Bye, Lily.
Bye. Bye, Teddy.

01:06.640 --> 01:09.314
Oh, my gosh, he's great!

01:09.440 --> 01:11.397
You're okay making plans with
my ex-boyfriend? [ Beeps ]

01:11.480 --> 01:13.915
Um, yes.
It's been a hundred years.

01:14.000 --> 01:16.560
Plus, this is one of the many benefits
of being gay.

01:16.680 --> 01:18.273
We can be friends with our exes...

01:18.360 --> 01:20.317
without all the petty jealousy
straight people go through.

01:20.400 --> 01:22.437
Well, I guess I am
friends with Pepper, so-

01:22.560 --> 01:24.916
I went on one date
with Pepper. One.

01:25.000 --> 01:26.957
When are you gonna stop
bringing it up?

01:27.040 --> 01:29.430
When you stop
reacting like that.

01:29.560 --> 01:32.200
Daddy loves Pepper.
I taught her that.

01:33.200 --> 01:34.016
♪ Hey, hey ♪

01:41.360 --> 01:42.510
♪ Hey♪ ♪

01:46.000 --> 01:47.434
That's private.

01:47.520 --> 01:49.876
Sorry. But why do you have
all of our names down on a list?

01:49.960 --> 01:51.599
It's for my school essay.

01:51.680 --> 01:52.796
"Pick a hero in your family...

01:52.880 --> 01:54.439
and write about
why you've chosen him or her."

01:54.520 --> 01:56.318
You're still in the running,

01:56.400 --> 01:58.517
but I'm not loving that you're drinking
wine while watching my brother.

01:58.600 --> 02:01.798
Well, it was from an open bottle
of white in your fridge, so-

02:01.880 --> 02:04.759
It's about judgment, Claire. It's
not the '70s. We know better.

02:04.840 --> 02:06.479
There was lipstick
on the bottle.

02:06.560 --> 02:08.437
There are my babies!

02:08.520 --> 02:10.158
- How was dinner?
- Perfect.

02:10.240 --> 02:11.879
I had a steak.
I had some ice cream.

02:11.960 --> 02:13.110
Gloria found
a hair in her fish,

02:13.200 --> 02:14.793
and it didn't cost us a penny!

02:14.920 --> 02:16.798
[ Laughing ] It might
have been my own hair,

02:16.880 --> 02:19.554
but Jay was so happy
that I didn't say anything.

02:19.640 --> 02:22.109
- What?
- Mm-hmm.

02:22.200 --> 02:24.396
Honey, you got a second before you go?
I wanna talk about something.

02:24.480 --> 02:26.880
- All right. Why is she smiling at me like that?
- [ Squeaks ]

02:26.920 --> 02:28.479
- It's good news.
- Okay.

02:28.560 --> 02:30.995
You remember Bob
from my office?

02:31.080 --> 02:33.959
Uncle Bob. The one who did the trick
where he'd pull the quarter out of my ear.

02:34.040 --> 02:36.111
He learned another trick. He pulled
50 grand out of our pension fund.

02:36.240 --> 02:37.230
Oh.
I fired him.

02:37.320 --> 02:38.470
But the worst part is,

02:38.560 --> 02:40.358
I was grooming him
to take over the company.

02:40.440 --> 02:41.510
But there's an upside.

02:41.640 --> 02:43.313
He wants you to work for him!

02:43.400 --> 02:44.754
I know it's just
a job right now,

02:44.840 --> 02:46.991
but you know that he has
this thing going on in his chest,

02:47.080 --> 02:49.241
so you never know where
you're going to end up, Claire!

02:49.360 --> 02:51.272
Mm-hmm. Mm-hmm. Gloria.
Gloria, it's a cold.

02:51.440 --> 02:52.794
Anyway, look.
Mmm.

02:52.880 --> 02:54.519
I know you've been wanting
to get back out there,

02:54.600 --> 02:56.557
and I always thought
that if you did go back to work,

02:56.640 --> 02:58.120
you'd come back
to work with me.

02:58.240 --> 03:00.516
I-I worked there for
half a summer 20 years ago.

03:00.600 --> 03:02.034
And it-
It was terrific, honey.

03:02.160 --> 03:04.152
Listen, obviously,
we'll start you out slow.

03:04.240 --> 03:06.311
We'll give you time
to relearn about the place...

03:06.400 --> 03:08.039
and then maybe move you up.

03:08.160 --> 03:10.356
You know, you do know a guy.
He means him!

03:10.440 --> 03:12.080
It's a wonderful opportunity,
Dad. Thanks.

03:12.160 --> 03:13.913
Could I think about it, talk to Phil?
Well, sure.

03:14.040 --> 03:15.474
I'll call you tomorrow.
All right. All right.

03:15.600 --> 03:17.193
Here's my boy. Give me my boy.
Here's your man.

03:17.320 --> 03:19.516
Here's little man. Oh, love him.
[ Muttering ]

03:19.600 --> 03:22.354
What did I say about these
flowered blankets for him?

03:22.480 --> 03:23.960
Ay.
Huh?

03:24.040 --> 03:26.714
He's starting to take after
Hugh Hefnerd over there.

03:26.800 --> 03:30.077
Very amusing, Jay.
Let me just get your name down here.

03:32.560 --> 03:34.756
Another brochure
from a community college.

03:34.840 --> 03:36.911
You know, I bet Mom
is having them send these.

03:37.000 --> 03:40.710
Really? You don't think they've
targeted you as a must-have recruit?

03:40.800 --> 03:42.757
At least this one doesn't have
that fakey lunchtime shot...

03:42.840 --> 03:44.672
of a black guy,
Asian girl and an Indian-

03:44.760 --> 03:46.797
Oh, wait! There it is.

03:46.880 --> 03:49.839
Wow, that wheelchair kid
is really cracking everybody up.

03:49.920 --> 03:51.877
[ Phil ] Girls, your mom's
on her way home with dinner!

03:52.000 --> 03:55.198
I never got this. If he sees it,
we'll have to talk about it.

03:57.320 --> 03:58.310
What?

03:58.400 --> 03:59.470
What what?

04:06.840 --> 04:08.718
If Grandpa calls, I'm not home.

04:08.840 --> 04:11.799
What happened? He wants
me to work for him.

04:11.880 --> 04:14.076
Like, groom me to take over
or something.

04:14.160 --> 04:15.560
I don't know
how I'm gonna say no.

04:15.640 --> 04:18.120
Why would you say no? I thought
you were looking for something.

04:18.160 --> 04:21.039
We could use the money, too, especially
if Haley decides to go back to school.

04:21.160 --> 04:24.437
Oh, is she still throwing out those
college brochures? Just tossed one now.

04:24.520 --> 04:26.432
Who does she think
empties the trash?

04:26.520 --> 04:28.955
You know what really sucks?
That job could be great.

04:29.080 --> 04:31.754
But my dad is a terrible boss.
He is so mean.

04:31.840 --> 04:33.957
"Princess, coffeepot's
not gonna wash itself."

04:34.080 --> 04:36.879
That's where you got that?
I said it to you one time.

04:36.960 --> 04:39.520
Well, you just gotta tell him
straight up, man-to-man.

04:39.600 --> 04:41.114
Woman-to-man.
You're very shapely.

04:41.200 --> 04:44.557
I know. I will.
It's just I hate it so much.

04:44.680 --> 04:48.640
The-The four big times that I
disappointed him, it devastated me.

04:48.720 --> 04:51.280
I mean, the first time,
I cut off all my hair.

04:51.360 --> 04:53.272
I went to college out of state.

04:53.360 --> 04:56.558
I crashed his vintage Jag
into a wall.

04:58.560 --> 05:00.040
That's only three.

05:00.120 --> 05:02.430
Kids, dinner!

05:04.680 --> 05:07.240
♪ ♪ [Pop]
Oh, loving this already.

05:07.320 --> 05:09.277
If no one gets a concussion,
we're totally coming back.

05:09.360 --> 05:12.876
So listen, if at any point you're not
okay with seeing me and Teddy together,

05:13.000 --> 05:14.673
just please let me know,
and we can go.

05:14.760 --> 05:16.479
Oh, well, thank you.
And if at any point...

05:16.560 --> 05:20.634
you're not okay with me being so
okay with it, you let me know.

05:20.720 --> 05:22.996
Teddy! Teddy! Hey!

05:23.120 --> 05:24.076
Ah, hey!
Hey!

05:24.160 --> 05:25.958
Oh, look at you!
[ Gasps ]

05:26.040 --> 05:28.714
This shirt is fantastic.
You're adorable.

05:28.800 --> 05:30.393
You're adorable!

05:30.480 --> 05:32.995
[ Singsongy ] Oh, I think
somebody has a crush!

05:33.080 --> 05:35.993
Thank you so much for having us. I don't
know which one of my girls is more excited.

05:36.120 --> 05:37.839
[ Laughs ] Here. Come on.
Let's get you some skates.

05:37.920 --> 05:39.195
I want Teddy to come.

05:39.280 --> 05:41.237
Oh, honey, I-I'm sure
Teddy has other things-

05:41.360 --> 05:43.158
No, no!
You guys go! Catch up.

05:43.280 --> 05:44.600
I'll lace up. [ Laughs ] Okay.

05:44.680 --> 05:46.239
Okay.
Come on. Ready?

05:46.360 --> 05:48.477
Have fun, okay!
Hey, Uncle Cam!

05:48.560 --> 05:50.791
Oh, my gosh! Hey!
What's-What's going on?

05:50.880 --> 05:52.792
What-What are you guys
doing here?

05:52.880 --> 05:54.917
- Teddy invited us.
- You guys know Teddy?

05:55.080 --> 05:56.514
Yeah, totally.
Yeah, Teddy's great.

05:56.600 --> 05:58.239
Heads up, amateurs!

05:58.320 --> 06:02.030
It's time to rock 'n' roll!
Do you get it?

06:02.120 --> 06:04.191
- Cam, what are you doing here?
- Um-

06:04.280 --> 06:06.875
- Oh, hell, it's Dad.
- Whose dad? Not your dad.

06:06.960 --> 06:08.952
[ Claire ] I have been
avoiding his calls all day.

06:09.040 --> 06:10.918
Quick, Phil, slingshot me.
All right.

06:11.040 --> 06:12.952
♪ ♪ [ Calypso]
Oh. Limbo skate, kids.

06:13.040 --> 06:15.555
How low can you go?

06:15.640 --> 06:18.553
I'm at a roller rink with my
family on a Saturday night.

06:18.640 --> 06:19.630
I win.

06:19.720 --> 06:21.791
I have got to get a photo
of Lily.

06:21.880 --> 06:23.519
Teddy's making her giggle
so hard.

06:23.600 --> 06:25.910
Oh, well, everybody
loves Teddy, so-

06:26.000 --> 06:28.515
But you'll let me know
if you're not okay.

06:28.600 --> 06:32.560
Mitchell, do you know your entire family's
here, invited by your ex-boyfriend?

06:32.640 --> 06:35.872
Phil and Claire, Jay and
Gloria, your cousin Pete.

06:35.960 --> 06:37.838
[ Mitchell ] Hey!

06:37.920 --> 06:39.912
Okay-It's a-
It's a fund-raiser, all right?

06:40.000 --> 06:42.356
I'm sure he just invited
everyone on his contact list.

06:44.280 --> 06:46.875
Oh, well, that makes sense.
Yes, of course it does.

06:47.000 --> 06:49.560
[ Chuckles ]
And... I'm flattered.

06:49.720 --> 06:52.076
Why are you flattered?
You know.

06:52.160 --> 06:54.277
- I don't.
- [ Singsongy ] You do.

06:56.240 --> 06:58.277
I really don't!

07:01.480 --> 07:03.995
Gloria, throw on those skates
and take a whirl with me.

07:04.080 --> 07:07.152
Oh, I totally would, but I'm taking
care of Lily, and she doesn't want to.

07:07.320 --> 07:08.390
Oh.
Yes, I do.

07:08.480 --> 07:10.039
No, you don't.
You told me before.

07:10.120 --> 07:12.476
You don't remember?
Why would I lie?

07:12.560 --> 07:16.156
Gloria, you don't know
how to roller-skate.

07:16.240 --> 07:19.631
Of course I do.
I know how to do everything.

07:21.400 --> 07:23.392
[ Groans ]
I can't lie to that face.

07:23.520 --> 07:26.911
It's a good thing that we're not married.
Well, I don't-

07:27.000 --> 07:29.640
I can't skate.
I am an elegant woman.

07:29.760 --> 07:33.993
That means that I never do the few
things that I don't really do that good.

07:34.080 --> 07:35.719
But I'm a natural teacher.

07:35.800 --> 07:37.632
But I'm going to look stupid.

07:37.720 --> 07:39.200
Gloria-

07:39.280 --> 07:41.078
Trust me.

07:41.160 --> 07:43.914
As long as you're standing next
to me, you will not look stupid.

07:44.960 --> 07:47.077
Oh, thank God!
There is no place to sit.

07:47.160 --> 07:49.311
Always room at my table
for my darling nieces.

07:49.400 --> 07:50.993
[ Groans ] You beat us to it.

07:51.080 --> 07:52.958
We were gonna ask this kid
if we could share.

07:53.080 --> 07:55.959
Well, he was just leaving. Yeah,
you could totally sit with us.

07:56.040 --> 07:58.555
You know, I debated
even putting you two on here.

08:01.200 --> 08:02.680
♪ ♪ [Pop] Whoa, fancy.

08:02.760 --> 08:05.036
Yeah, I know. Well, I
did use to work here.

08:05.120 --> 08:07.999
W-W-Wait. You're the
Claire from the bathroom?

08:08.080 --> 08:09.560
Oh, is it still here?

08:09.640 --> 08:11.120
Y-Yeah. [ Laughs ] Oh.

08:11.200 --> 08:13.999
Oh! Hey! Look at you two,
catching up after all these years.

08:14.080 --> 08:16.231
It hasn't been that long. It's
been a month since you came by...

08:16.360 --> 08:18.192
when Alex had the flu, right?
Oh, no kiddin'?

08:18.280 --> 08:20.840
I do get a home-cooked meal out of it.
Plus I owe these guys.

08:20.960 --> 08:22.561
Phil helped me buy my
last two houses. Oh.

08:22.600 --> 08:25.672
[ Chuckles ] So good. Such great stories.
[ Laughs ]

08:25.760 --> 08:28.355
[ Jay ] Hey, you! You
owe me a phone call.

08:28.440 --> 08:32.229
I know! I'm gonna call you!
Hey! Teddy's here, huh?

08:32.320 --> 08:35.279
Yeah, deadbeat. You owe
me 50 bucks for the golf.

08:35.360 --> 08:37.669
Well, maybe I'll slip it to you
during your next prostate exam.

08:37.760 --> 08:40.719
- I'll bet you're counting the days, you perv.
- [ Laughs ]

08:40.799 --> 08:44.077
Oh. So funny. You and Jay really
seem to have a thing, don't ya?

08:44.159 --> 08:46.720
And Gloria-What's the nature
of your relationship with her?

08:46.800 --> 08:48.519
Well, actually,
we just met tonight.

08:48.640 --> 08:51.678
You know, I'm not so sure
she likes me. Really?

08:51.800 --> 08:54.474
Oh, well, I mean, she just takes
a little time to warm up.

08:54.560 --> 08:57.234
Oh, thanks. And thank you,
again, for coming tonight.

08:57.320 --> 09:01.280
With the money we raised, we'll be able
to inoculate over 4,000 needy kids...

09:01.360 --> 09:03.636
against some
truly awful diseases.

09:04.680 --> 09:06.558
And how well do you know Luke?

09:06.640 --> 09:08.199
I love that movie too!
[ Giggles ]

09:08.280 --> 09:10.795
Yeah, that cool fight scene
on that skyscraper in Shanghai-

09:10.880 --> 09:12.473
It really made me
want to go to Japan.

09:12.560 --> 09:13.994
Why? Shanghai's in China.

09:14.080 --> 09:15.878
I'm just saying,
you don't want to fly to Japan,

09:15.960 --> 09:17.952
get in a cab and say,
"Take me to downtown Shanghai."

09:18.040 --> 09:20.953
It's a pretty expensive ride.
[ Laughs ]

09:21.080 --> 09:23.276
Um, I'm gonna go
to the bathroom.

09:23.360 --> 09:26.353
Come with me.
Be right back, guys.

09:27.760 --> 09:30.116
Uh, what do you think
you're doing out there?

09:30.240 --> 09:32.835
I'm flirting. [ Sighs ]
That's what I was afraid of.

09:32.920 --> 09:34.991
I'm not gonna pretend I'm stupid
just so a boy will like me.

09:35.080 --> 09:38.551
Of course not. But you don't have
to put the poor guy to shame.

09:38.680 --> 09:42.560
Flirting with boys is about increasing
your value, not decreasing theirs.

09:42.640 --> 09:45.872
That's a complicated thought.
What magazine taught you that?

09:45.960 --> 09:47.633
You're doing it again!
The mean thing.

09:47.720 --> 09:49.951
Can you even hear it or what?

09:50.040 --> 09:51.872
I heard it.
Good.

09:51.960 --> 09:55.749
So now that he knows that you're
smart, let's work on being nice.

09:55.880 --> 09:57.439
Wanna ditch the hoodie? No.

09:57.520 --> 09:59.239
It's all good.
It's a process.

09:59.320 --> 10:02.950
Man, tough finding a hero
in this family, huh?

10:03.080 --> 10:05.276
You know,
I've got problems of my own.

10:05.360 --> 10:08.273
I can't always be the lovable
sidekick on The Manny Show.

10:08.360 --> 10:10.272
Did you even notice
I'm binge eating?

10:10.360 --> 10:13.558
Whoa. You're really
going through something.

10:13.680 --> 10:15.876
Wanna talk about it?
Not even a little bit.

10:15.960 --> 10:18.270
And don't go hounding me
like you always do.

10:18.360 --> 10:20.716
Well, thanks for restoring
my faith in this family.

10:20.800 --> 10:22.996
Too bad I'm not related to Teddy.
He seems terrific.

10:23.080 --> 10:25.037
Doesn't he, though?

10:25.120 --> 10:26.759
Knees bent.

10:26.840 --> 10:30.277
Arms loose. Chin up.
Butt out.

10:30.400 --> 10:32.119
Ay, no, Phil.
This is too much!

10:32.240 --> 10:33.833
No, just remember
"KBALCUBO." Huh?

10:33.960 --> 10:37.271
K-B-A-L-C-U-B-O. "Koala bears always
lose cherries under big overpasses."

10:37.400 --> 10:39.480
Ay, no! How am I gonna remember all that?
Uh, uh, oh!

10:39.520 --> 10:40.954
Oh! Aah!
I gotcha.

10:41.040 --> 10:42.360
[ Laughing ]
Ay. Ay.

10:42.480 --> 10:44.312
Ay, Teddy-
Teddy, you're amazing!

10:44.400 --> 10:46.756
[ Laughing ] Thank
you for saving me!

10:46.880 --> 10:48.997
Let me get in there, boys. Excuse me.
[ Video Game Beeping ]

10:49.080 --> 10:50.400
[ Inhales ] Boom!

10:50.480 --> 10:51.675
[ Bells Clanging ]
[ Sirens Wailing ]

10:51.760 --> 10:54.912
Okay! Okay,
clearly it's time to talk.

10:55.000 --> 10:57.595
All right, Cam.
Cam, you're obviously upset.

10:57.680 --> 11:00.991
But trust me. There are no lingering
feelings between me and Teddy.

11:01.080 --> 11:02.560
I don't care about
you and Teddy.

11:02.680 --> 11:04.961
I don't like what's lingering
between him and your family.

11:05.080 --> 11:06.753
What?
Mitchell, look around.

11:06.840 --> 11:09.230
Your family is cheating on
me with your ex-boyfriend.

11:09.320 --> 11:11.400
Cheating-Okay, yes.
Th-There is a bit more contact...

11:11.440 --> 11:13.113
between them
than I realized, but-

11:13.200 --> 11:16.511
Oh, oh. Now this is where we make Cam
the oversensitive drama queen.

11:16.600 --> 11:19.559
God forbid we take any action
to make things right for me.

11:19.640 --> 11:21.360
Well, okay. Okay,
what do you want me to do?

11:21.400 --> 11:25.235
Would you like me to ask
them to break up with Teddy?

11:25.320 --> 11:27.121
- Is that what you're asking?
- Of course not.

11:27.160 --> 11:29.560
- I would never ask that. That would be insane.
- Well, good.

11:29.600 --> 11:31.353
It would be as insane
for me to ask that...

11:31.440 --> 11:33.591
as it would be sane
for you to offer it.

11:33.680 --> 11:35.558
So that is what you're asking.

11:35.640 --> 11:37.154
No, that's what I'm not asking.

11:37.240 --> 11:39.880
But if you decide to do it,
I want it to come from you, not me,

11:39.960 --> 11:41.917
because I'm clearly
not asking for it.

11:42.040 --> 11:44.111
Okay, this is nuts.
Is it?

11:44.200 --> 11:47.272
I worked my fingers to the bone
to get these jumpy Protestants to love me,

11:47.360 --> 11:51.718
and now I find out they're holding a
torch for the man who came before me?

11:51.800 --> 11:54.474
It's not nuts.
It's actually quite painful.

11:54.560 --> 11:56.836
Excuse me, sir?
You just won a prize...

11:56.920 --> 11:58.957
for setting a rink record
on the boxing machine.

11:59.040 --> 12:01.032
If you wouldn't mind taking a
picture for our wall of fame?

12:01.120 --> 12:02.873
Oh, yeah, sure. Absolutely.
Just one second.

12:02.960 --> 12:04.872
Okay.
That's exciting.

12:04.960 --> 12:06.952
Mitchell, I know
you'll do what's right.

12:07.080 --> 12:09.470
Unless you like
seeing me humiliated?

12:10.640 --> 12:11.994
Thank you.

12:12.080 --> 12:15.073
[ Skates Clomping ]

12:20.000 --> 12:22.276
Everybody was staring, Phil.

12:22.360 --> 12:24.238
What if we practice outside
where no one can see us?

12:24.320 --> 12:28.314
[ Hiccups ] Ay, and now I
have the nervous burps!

12:28.400 --> 12:29.754
Oh. I'm s-
Claire.

12:29.840 --> 12:31.911
Dad? Wh-What are you
doing out here?

12:32.000 --> 12:33.992
Apparently, this is the only
way we'll get to talk tonight.

12:34.080 --> 12:35.560
About this job-
Mm-hmm?

12:35.680 --> 12:38.115
Hey, guys. This sounds really
important, Dad. Hang on.

12:38.200 --> 12:39.761
- Go ahead, Mitchell.
- Okay, so listen.

12:39.800 --> 12:41.200
This is coming from me.
No one else.

12:41.360 --> 12:42.880
Mm-hmm? But I need
you to do something.

12:42.920 --> 12:45.081
- And I don't want you to give me any flak.
- Aw, geez.

12:45.200 --> 12:46.714
That's flak.
I-I think it's a little weird...

12:46.840 --> 12:49.594
how you all still hang out
with Teddy so much. Told you.

12:49.680 --> 12:53.754
And I think it would be appropriate if maybe
you all, you know, stopped seeing him.

12:53.840 --> 12:55.638
- This is coming from Cam, isn't it?
- [ Clicks Tongue ]

12:55.720 --> 12:57.234
No, it's not.

12:57.320 --> 12:58.959
Wait a second.

12:59.040 --> 13:01.919
Cam doesn't think we can love
him and Teddy at the same time?

13:02.000 --> 13:04.469
And you just sold Cam out
like that. Wow.

13:06.040 --> 13:09.078
What is that? I'll tell you what it is.
It's sad.

13:09.160 --> 13:11.595
[Man On P.A. ] Hey, skaters!
Not an emergency,

13:11.680 --> 13:13.592
but we do have a small fire
in the snack bar.

13:13.680 --> 13:16.639
We'd like everyone
to calmly file outside. Thanks.

13:16.720 --> 13:18.598
Okay, everyone,
the exit's over here.

13:18.680 --> 13:21.070
Come this way, please.
This way, to the exit.

13:21.160 --> 13:23.311
All right, everybody over here.

13:23.400 --> 13:24.880
You guys, just do this for me.

13:24.960 --> 13:26.917
But... he's all the way
over there.

13:27.000 --> 13:29.231
There's no hurry. We're in a
wooden box built in 1970.

13:29.360 --> 13:30.635
Let's go!
All right, let's go.

13:30.720 --> 13:32.598
Okay, well, thank you.
That's very nice.

13:32.720 --> 13:33.756
Okay.
Sweet of you.

13:33.840 --> 13:35.718
Hey, skaters, good news!

13:35.800 --> 13:38.952
Fire's out!
Sorry for the scare.

13:40.240 --> 13:41.754
All right,
before you get upset,

13:41.880 --> 13:43.519
this was just about
convenience.

13:43.600 --> 13:44.590
Was it?
Mm-hmm.

13:44.680 --> 13:46.478
Or was it a perfect metaphor?

13:46.560 --> 13:51.396
Congratulations, Mitchell. This is as
sad as I've ever been in roller skates.

13:53.760 --> 13:56.878
Okay, be careful.
I don't want to get hurt, okay?

13:57.000 --> 13:59.117
No one's gonna get hurt.
[ Shouts ] Hold on!

13:59.200 --> 14:00.190
Ow! That hurts!

14:00.280 --> 14:02.158
[ Grunting ] Okay, if
we could just-Ah!

14:02.320 --> 14:04.357
Son of a Mitchell!
Ah!

14:04.440 --> 14:06.671
Do not worry one bit.

14:06.760 --> 14:08.717
You are gettin' it.

14:08.800 --> 14:10.792
Let's get away
from the cars, huh?

14:12.840 --> 14:14.832
Disgusting.

14:14.960 --> 14:17.600
Claire Pritchett?
Jeff?

14:17.680 --> 14:19.831
No way! I haven't seen you
since you worked here.

14:20.000 --> 14:23.357
Oh, wow! You-You still do.
Yeah, do what you love,

14:23.480 --> 14:25.676
you never work a day in
your life, right? Uh-huh.

14:25.800 --> 14:27.519
This is perfect. Some civilian
just yakked in the rink.

14:27.600 --> 14:29.080
Can you take over for a minute?

14:29.160 --> 14:30.913
Um, uh, no.
[ Chuckles ]

14:31.000 --> 14:32.680
It's kind of where
I make most of my money.

14:32.800 --> 14:34.598
You know, I hate to shut it down.
Mmm.

14:34.680 --> 14:37.400
I got a girl pregnant.
It's a whole thing.

14:37.560 --> 14:39.153
All right. I'll do it for a minute.
Sure. Great.

14:39.280 --> 14:40.396
Thank you. Thank you. Okay.

14:40.520 --> 14:42.398
Oh, hey.
Yeah?

14:42.480 --> 14:43.960
I still think about that kiss.

14:45.360 --> 14:47.397
- [ Laughs ]
- Uh-huh.

14:47.480 --> 14:49.870
Oh, God.

14:49.960 --> 14:52.111
[ Grunts ] Yes.

14:52.200 --> 14:53.680
Mom, I threw up.

14:53.760 --> 14:56.480
Oh, honey, that was you?
You gonna be okay?

14:56.560 --> 14:58.279
Let me get you something
for your tummy.

14:58.400 --> 15:00.392
[ Ice Crunches ]
I'm just so stressed out.

15:00.480 --> 15:03.518
- You know that hero essay I have to write?
- Mm-hmm?

15:03.600 --> 15:05.441
Well, Dad kind of assumed
I wrote it about him.

15:05.560 --> 15:07.074
Mm-hmm.
But I didn't.

15:07.160 --> 15:10.198
And now he wants to read it,
and I don't know what to do.

15:10.280 --> 15:12.317
Don't worry about your father.
I am sure he'll understand.

15:12.400 --> 15:15.279
Claire, I need some ice
for Cameron.

15:15.360 --> 15:17.352
And we have to talk about
the job.

15:17.440 --> 15:18.920
Unless you've taken back
this one.

15:19.000 --> 15:20.514
Dad, I'm with a customer
right now.

15:20.600 --> 15:22.478
I'll be with you
in just a moment.

15:24.840 --> 15:26.593
Honey, I'll talk to your dad.

15:26.680 --> 15:28.797
You don't think he'll be
upset I wrote it about you?

15:28.880 --> 15:30.519
You wrote it about me?

15:30.600 --> 15:32.592
Mom, you know me and homework.

15:32.680 --> 15:35.479
I didn't give it much thought.
What's a hero?

15:35.560 --> 15:39.713
Someone who's not afraid of anything
and who's strong-That's you.

15:39.800 --> 15:41.393
But Dad's so great too.

15:41.520 --> 15:43.239
Oh, here it comes.
Okay. All right.

15:43.360 --> 15:44.953
You just sit down. Sit down, sweet pea.
[ Groaning ]

15:45.040 --> 15:46.599
Have your drink.
You're gonna be fine.

15:46.680 --> 15:49.593
[ Inhales ] Okay.

15:49.680 --> 15:52.036
Here goes. Um-

15:52.120 --> 15:55.636
So, Dad, the last time
we worked together,

15:55.720 --> 15:57.313
it was tense between us.

15:57.400 --> 15:59.790
- What? No, it wasn't.
- Yes, it was.

15:59.880 --> 16:02.873
You were-You were really hard on
me, and you talked down to me.

16:02.960 --> 16:05.191
- You don't know what you're talking about.
- Right.

16:05.280 --> 16:07.556
And when I confronted you,
like I am doing now,

16:07.640 --> 16:10.872
you were insensitive,
like you are being now.

16:10.960 --> 16:12.952
And while I really
appreciate the opportunity,

16:13.040 --> 16:14.554
and I do love you very much,

16:14.640 --> 16:17.360
I don't think that working
together is a very good idea.

16:20.120 --> 16:21.600
- All right, fine.
- Mm-hmm.

16:21.680 --> 16:23.831
I'm not gonna lie.
I'm very disappointed.

16:24.640 --> 16:26.916
[ Clicks Tongue ]

16:27.000 --> 16:28.593
[ Exhales ]

16:29.600 --> 16:31.432
- [ Haley ] Yeah!
- We won!

16:31.520 --> 16:34.115
- Man, that sucks!
- Yeah, totally unmasculating.

16:34.200 --> 16:36.431
Well, at least you guys
look cool when you play.

16:36.520 --> 16:38.512
Let's play again.
This never happened.

16:38.640 --> 16:41.314
Actually, we need to go hang out
with our family for a while.

16:41.400 --> 16:42.880
Really? Now?

16:42.960 --> 16:45.919
Yeah, but we'll be around.
We'll see you guys.

16:46.000 --> 16:48.037
Wh-What happened?
Did I mess up?

16:48.160 --> 16:49.560
No, you did great.
So he didn't like me.

16:49.680 --> 16:51.751
No, he totally liked you.
Then why'd we walk away?

16:51.840 --> 16:54.912
This was never about him. This is
about getting you some confidence.

16:55.000 --> 16:56.753
Guys will pick up on that.
Better guys.

16:56.840 --> 16:59.753
Guys who can lose to a girl
without feeling emasculated.

17:01.880 --> 17:04.395
Okay, try not to throw this
in my face one day,

17:04.480 --> 17:06.392
but sometimes
you're actually really smart.

17:06.480 --> 17:10.156
Like, smart smart.
I hope you know that.

17:11.480 --> 17:13.472
Wow.

17:13.560 --> 17:14.596
Thanks.

17:17.800 --> 17:20.481
And I'm totally throwing that in
your face one day. Are you kidding?

17:22.560 --> 17:24.869
Oh, thank you so much.
Everything go okay?

17:24.960 --> 17:26.758
No. Actually, I was
trapped back here,

17:26.839 --> 17:28.319
my dad and I got
in a whole thing.

17:28.440 --> 17:30.033
Now he's mad at me.

17:30.120 --> 17:33.033
- Oh, where'd you find that?
- I know where you keep the beer, Jeff.

17:33.120 --> 17:36.716
I hate this feeling! I swear, it
started when I was 12 years old...

17:36.800 --> 17:38.553
and I got a "C"
in social studies.

17:38.640 --> 17:42.395
The way my dad looked at me, you would have
thought I'd worn a tube top in church.

17:42.480 --> 17:45.040
He knew it crushed me.
He didn't care.

17:45.960 --> 17:47.394
That's why I can't work
for him.

17:47.480 --> 17:50.040
He was hard on me then.
He's gonna be hard on me now.

17:50.120 --> 17:53.192
Telling you,
people don't change.

17:53.280 --> 17:56.239
I've changed. I don't wanna
put up with this stuff.

17:56.320 --> 17:59.552
I am a completely different
person than I was 20 years ago.

17:59.680 --> 18:02.718
All right, kids.
That's gonna be 18.50.

18:02.800 --> 18:06.476
Out of 20?
Here's your $1.50-

18:06.560 --> 18:08.950
I thought so.

18:09.040 --> 18:10.872
[ Sighs ]

18:10.960 --> 18:14.954
Well, I mean, do you feel good that
you were at least honest with him?

18:15.040 --> 18:17.714
No. And... super no.

18:17.800 --> 18:21.080
Because I'm the one who's left with this
awful feeling every time I disappoint him.

18:21.120 --> 18:23.760
It's not fair. 'Cause I'm not
the bad guy here.

18:23.840 --> 18:26.355
He needs to know that.

18:31.040 --> 18:32.474
How's that?
[ Groans ]

18:32.600 --> 18:36.037
Is that better? Yeah, much better.
Tha-Thank you, Teddy.

18:36.120 --> 18:38.396
You're fixed!
Skate with me!

18:38.480 --> 18:40.073
I think it's a little soon,
sweetie.

18:40.160 --> 18:43.073
- No. Teddy.
- But-Oh, sure thing, kiddo.

18:43.160 --> 18:45.001
Hey, lots of ice,
no cartwheels for three days.

18:45.040 --> 18:46.713
[ Chuckles ] Yeah.

18:46.800 --> 18:48.234
Ready? Come on.

18:48.360 --> 18:52.115
Good guy. Who? Teddy? Yeah.
Yeah, he's the best.

18:52.200 --> 18:54.840
Nuts he can't
find anybody, huh?

18:54.920 --> 18:57.116
Gotta be something
a little off there.

18:57.240 --> 19:00.916
He definitely did not bring out the best in Mitchell.
I can tell you that right now.

19:01.000 --> 19:02.639
Oh, really?

19:02.720 --> 19:05.474
Well, you know, not that it
matters, but in what way exactly?

19:05.560 --> 19:08.234
Honestly?
When they were together,

19:08.320 --> 19:10.357
Mitchell could be a bit of a pill.
Oh.

19:10.440 --> 19:15.356
Now, I like Teddy, but when they
broke up, I was actually kinda glad.

19:15.440 --> 19:19.070
Of course, Mitchell thought that I was
uncomfortable because of the gay thing,

19:19.160 --> 19:21.038
and maybe I was, but...

19:21.120 --> 19:23.476
I really just want him
to be happy,

19:23.560 --> 19:26.155
like he is now.

19:26.240 --> 19:29.916
And when you two started up, everyone
thought, "Well, there it is."

19:31.600 --> 19:34.069
Okay, kids. Couples' skate.

19:34.200 --> 19:37.511
Grab someone you love and get out there.
[ Inhales ]

19:37.600 --> 19:39.159
[ Voice Breaking ]
Jay, you can be so-

19:39.320 --> 19:41.755
I'm not skating with you, Cam.
Yeah.

19:41.840 --> 19:45.675
What about me, Dad?
You wanna skate with me?

19:45.760 --> 19:47.558
♪ ♪ [Piano, Ballad]

19:47.640 --> 19:50.280
[Manny] What qualifies
someone as a hero?

19:50.400 --> 19:55.429
♪ ♪ [Man Singing, indistinct] Obviously,
a hero has to be someone we respect-

19:55.560 --> 19:57.631
[ Laughing ]
a person we look up to,

19:57.720 --> 20:00.713
a person who is generous
of spirit-

20:00.800 --> 20:04.271
- Hey!
- Hi. Hi.

20:04.360 --> 20:05.874
Who's willing
to grow and learn.

20:05.960 --> 20:09.237
So, Dad, if that offer
still stands-

20:09.320 --> 20:11.596
Really?
What changed?

20:11.680 --> 20:13.911
[ Clicks Tongue ]
A couple of things.

20:14.000 --> 20:16.469
Maybe it's the person
you love most in the world...

20:16.560 --> 20:19.951
or the guy who makes the most out
of life, no matter what anyone thinks.

20:20.080 --> 20:21.992
[ Shouting ] It's cool! Now
everybody's laughing at me!

20:22.120 --> 20:24.919
Keep rolling! This is your chance!
Ay, no! No!

20:25.000 --> 20:27.469
Yeah!

20:27.600 --> 20:30.354
[ Claire ] Phil! I know.

20:30.440 --> 20:32.591
For me, though-
Go, Dad!

20:32.680 --> 20:35.070
The hero in my family
is my family,

20:35.160 --> 20:38.153
because of who we are together.

20:45.120 --> 20:47.760
C-minus.
"This was not the assignment."

20:47.840 --> 20:51.516
I'll tell you who's not my
hero-Mrs. Rita McNabb.

20:55.720 --> 20:57.200
[ Phil ] Yeah.
[ Cheering ]

20:57.280 --> 20:58.953
Oh, thank you! Thank you!

20:59.040 --> 21:00.633
What is everybody looking at?

21:00.720 --> 21:02.480
I guess I could tell
the story one more time.

21:02.520 --> 21:04.034
Sure, yeah. Well, I was
mad about something.

21:04.120 --> 21:05.793
I don't even remember what.

21:05.880 --> 21:07.519
I turned-
Now, at this point,

21:07.600 --> 21:09.432
I'm more animal
than I am man-

21:09.520 --> 21:11.477
strike the punching machine,

21:11.560 --> 21:13.711
and apparently I broke
some sort of world record.

21:13.800 --> 21:15.280
I guess the thing that
I'll never forget...

21:15.360 --> 21:16.840
is the sound that it made.

21:16.960 --> 21:19.953
It was, like, bells
and whistles and sirens.

21:20.040 --> 21:21.793
It's impossible to describe.

21:21.880 --> 21:24.236
[ Bell Clanging ]
[ Sirens Wailing ]

21:24.320 --> 21:26.320
That is literally the first punch
I've ever thrown!

21:26.360 --> 21:28.158
[ Laughs ] [ Stops ]

21:28.280 --> 21:30.715
You are never to see him again.
Yes, I know.
